I love going to conferences. It’s hands down one of my favorite ways to network. There is so much going on between the parties and the conference floor. And this one was at the Broadmoor so it was extra fancy 🥰 

I got to catch up with old friends and I also made some new ones. Thanks @nocohempexpo and @morrisbeegle for putting on such an amazing show! There was a s’more bar at the First Citizen Bank party, which is a hemp friendly bank and such a nice group of people. If you’re looking for banking and your in hemp and CBD you should check them out! #conference #nocohempexpo2023 #broadmoor #hempderived

About a month ago we lost Anson’s dad to a disease called Aphasia. It is a little different then Alzheimer’s in the sense that he still had cognitive abilities. But his brain and body didn’t really communicate so his body slowly started to shut down. He went into a memory care facility about 6 months ago and anson and I went every week as we watched the disease progress.

About a month ago he was released from that pain. We were able to celebrate him this past weekend with so many loved ones around on the beautiful property that Bill built from nothing, and loved so much. RIP Bill Mitchell! You will be missed ❤️ #rip
